![](images/var_names_2.PNG)

. . .

<br>

La función `janitor::clean_names()` elimina los caracteres especiales e implementa el estilo **snake case** como estilo predeterminado:

::: {.cell hash='index_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-26_27e093c9c2997488949692fa02b312a0'}

```{.r .cell-code}
df_clean <- df_raw |> 
  janitor::clean_names() 
```
:::

![](images/var_names_3.PNG)

## Eliminar columnas o filas vacías

::: panel-tabset
### Problema

::: {.cell hash='index_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-27_d0fcf89b2fd90a66591a629602be6769'}

```{.r .cell-code}
df_clean |> 
  select(pat_id, race:start_bp) |> 
  slice(13:18)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
# A tibble: 6 × 5
  pat_id race             dob                 x7    start_bp
  <chr>  <chr>            <dttm>              <lgl> <chr>   
